    <li>
        Data Protection Indemnity
        <ol>
            <li>For the purpose of the Data Protection Act 1998, you acknowledge that in the course of you using the services that We provide or advertising goods or services on our Website, certain personal data about you, your employees, agents or subcontractors or certain personal data of third parties appearing in the advertising you requested to appear on our Website may be captured electronically or otherwise by us. If this is the case, you shall ensure that you have obtained the express consent of any employees, agents, subcontractors or any applicable third parties to the transfer of their personal data to us to use, store and process such personal information for the purposes set out in this Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy, including where such personal data forms part of the advertising and is posted to the Website for accessed by users inside and outside of the European Economic Area. You shall indemnify JobLadder from and against all claims by any employees, agents, subcontractors or any third parties arising out of your failure to obtain the consent described in this paragraph 8.</li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
        Changes to Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy
        <ol>
            <li>We reserve the right to add to or change the terms of this Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy in our sole discretion, without prior notice to you. If We change this Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy, We will post the new Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy on the Website, and it will become effective from the time of posting to the Website. Please visit this Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy on a regular basis to make sure you have read the latest version and you understand what We do with your information. Wherever possible, We will give you notice of any changes prior to their implementation.</li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
        Feedback
        <ol>
